Issue Type: <b>Feature Request</b>

Add Activation Events for setting field.

This allows precise control over when expansion needs to be activated.

Reduce unnecessary extensions runs.

Reduce memory usage and speed.

```diff
onLanguage:${language}
onCommand:${command}
onDebug
workspaceContains:${toplevelfilename}
onFileSystem:${scheme}
onView:${viewId}
*
+ onSetting: ${key}==${value}
+ onSettingExist: ${key}
+ onSettingUpdate: ${key}
```

### Why should I need it?

some extension, they need to be activated when user set the relative config.

for example: when user seted `sync.autoDownload` then actived the extension [Settings Sync](https://github.com/shanalikhan/code-settings-sync) and download the setting.

```json
{
  "sync.autoDownload": true
}
```

set `activationEvents`

```diff
{
  "activationEvents": [
-   "*"
+   "onSetting: sync.autoDownload==true",
+   "onSettingUpdate: sync.autoDownload"
  ]
}
```

So, `Settings Sync` don't need to activating and check `sync.autoDownload` the field exists or not.

**In theory, it can reduce the self-starting of a part of the extension, which should improve performance.**

